<br>
2) No posts may be made anonymously. Your characters name in game must be made known in your post, at the bottom if possible, if you are to put another character's name on the Most-Hated list.<br>
<br>
3) MOST posts are given a trial lifespan of 7 days. During this time, players may add other similar things happening with the listed player or guild, defend them, etc. However, the lifespan of a post is not guaranteed. Posts such as &quot;JoeDr00d didn't port me to EC&quot; will be deleted on sight, as will any posts that are deemed by the moderators to be unworthy of even a trial.<br>
<br>
4) During this 7 day period, if the story is still being uncovered or added to, the post will be allowed to stay until a relative period of stasis. At the end of this period, it will be determined by the moderators whether or not this person or guild is going to be deleted or remain on the list.<br>
<br>
5) Players that are deemed worthy of their placement here will be kept on the Most-Hated list permanently. To be deemed worthy means that there has been enough testimony and evidence brought forth to make a substantial case. In the world of EQ, 100% proof is nearly impossible to come by, but common sense and good judgement are more than enough.<br>
<br>
6) Posts that are deemed insufficient based on their merits will be locked and taken down, with an explanation given by the moderator. In some cases the explanation may be left open so players can respond, but in many, the case is closed when the moderator renders it so.<br>
